      "description": "User-mode networking daemons for virtual machines and namespaces",
      "note": "Fixes:\n- possible abnormal terminations of loopback connections in pasta(1), https://bugs.passt.top/show_bug.cgi?id=202\n- failure to start when IPv4/IPv6 neighbours are added while we're reading them, https://bugs.passt.top/show_bug.cgi?id=203\n- local forwarding with -T / -U in pasta on IPv6-only setups, https://bugs.passt.top/show_bug.cgi?id=205\n- SELinux policy prevents pesto(1), when pasta(1) is started by Podman, to configure port forwarding https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/28478\n\n\n----\n\n- introduce pesto(1), a client to configure port forwarding of existing passt and pasta instances\n- fix a significant throughput regression especially visible on connections with low but non-negligible RTT (100 - 500 \u00b5s)",
