      "security": false,
      "update_type": "enhancement",
      "severity": "medium",
      "cves": null,
      "description": "Daemon that finds starving tasks and gives them a temporary boost",
      "note": "version bump to v1.27.1\n    \n      User-facing changes:\n    \n      * Make syslog logging opt-in by default\n        Previously syslog was always enabled with no way to disable it.\n        Now syslog is opt-in via -s/--log_syslog flag. The systemd service\n        file has been updated to explicitly enable syslog.\n    \n      * Die on invalid CPU affinity\n        Previously stalld silently ignored invalid -a/--affinity arguments.\n        Now stalld exits with an error on invalid CPU affinity settings.\n    \n      Test infrastructure:\n    \n      * Improved test reliability with event-driven detection replacing\n        fixed sleeps, added pass()/fail() helpers, and fixed various test bugs\n        (33 commits)\n    \n    Signed-off-by: Clark Williams <williams@redhat.com>",
      "bodhi_url": "https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2026-038b8cd1a2"
    },
